OL,6,FMr Keir, 99, of Bakewell, left school
OL,7,Faged 14 and was an apprentice painter
OL,8,Fand decorator, and around 1939 he
OL,9,Fhelped to camouflage hydro-electric
OL,10,Fdams and buildings before joining the
OL,11,FRoyal Navy in 1943 when he was 18.
OL,13,FAs a Royal Navy seaman he carried out
OL,14,Fgeneral ship and gunnery duties on his
OL,15,Fship, the Flower class corvette HMS
OL,16,FPotentilla.
