OL,6,FHe was part of the naval crew that
OL,7,Fferried US troops onto Utah beach on D-
OL,8,FDay on 6 June, 1944, and he was
OL,9,Fawarded the National Order of the
OL,10,FLegion of Honour (Legion d'honneur) by
OL,11,Fthe French Government in 2015 for his
OL,12,Fheroism.
OL,14,FThe Legion d'honneur is the highest
OL,15,FFrench order of merit for both
OL,16,Fmilitary and civilian personnel and Mr
OL,17,FKeir received his medal from the Lord
OL,18,FLieutenant of Derbyshire at a service
OL,19,Fat Bakewell Church.
