OL,3,CD-Day veteran looks set to receive
OL,4,Chonour of freedom of Derbyshire
OL,6,FFollowing the Second World War, Mr
OL,7,FKeir worked as a painter and decorator
OL,8,Ffor Derbyshire County Council, but
OL,9,Fleft to work at Furness and Hassels in
OL,10,FLongstone before returning to the
OL,11,Fcounty council in the 1960s.
OL,13,FHe retired around 1990 aged 65.
OL,15,FMr Keir married Dorothy in 1954 and
OL,16,Fthey were together for 66 years,
OL,17,Fhaving one son, Andrew. Dorothy died
OL,18,Faged 87 in 2019.
