OL,6,FHe has another son, Michael, from a
OL,7,Fprevious marriage and two
OL,8,Fgrandchildren from him.
OL,10,FTo honour the memory of fallen
OL,11,Fcomrades, Mr Keir sold poppies for the
OL,12,FRoyal British Legion, becoming one of
OL,13,Fthe longest serving poppy sellers in
OL,14,Fthe country.
OL,16,FHe returned to Normandy in June this
OL,17,Fyear with other veterans to mark the
OL,18,F80th anniversary of D-Day. While there
OL,19,Fhe met HM King Charles and HM Queen
OL,20,FCamilla, among other dignitaries.
